On Earth, all living creatures are interconnected – from tiny insects to giant mammals, from delicate flowers to towering trees. Elements of nature like sunlight, water and air make it possible for life to exist. On this year's Earth Day, we celebrate all life on the planet. (Cover image via CFP. Video filmed by CGTN Nature film crew, edited by CGTN's Zhao Ying, voiceover by CGTN's Ge Ning.) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)